I"n<h2 id="creating-digital-exhibits-a-survey-of-tools">Creating Digital Exhibits: A Survey of Tools</h2>

<p>This workshop will cover an assortment of digital exhibit and storytelling tools such as Omeka, Scalar, static site generators (CollectionBuilder and Wax), and narrative tools such as Timeline.js and Storymaps from Knight Lab.</p>

<p>This session is part of the <a href="https://libcal.library.ubc.ca/calendar/vancouver/?t=g&amp;q=Digital%20toolkit&amp;cid=7544&amp;cal=7544&amp;inc=0">Digital Toolkit series</a> co-presented by the <a href="https://researchcommons.library.ubc.ca/">UBC Library Research Commons at UBC-V</a> and <a href="https://library.ok.ubc.ca/">UBC-O Library</a>.</p>

<h2 id="learning-objectives">Learning objectives</h2>

<p>At the end of this session, you will be able to:</p>
<ol>
  <li>List common tools and what they might be useful for</li>
  <li>Identify hosting resources at UBC and beyond</li>
</ol>

